cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.DB. 

The paper deals with the problem of mapping road networks using machine learning techniques and integrating them into existing map editing workflows. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for inferring road topology from aerial imagery, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for building the machine-assisted map editing system, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for designing the user interface, and database systems (cs.DB) for storing and managing the map data. Additionally, the paper focuses on the visualization and manipulation of geographic data, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
